resources.name: Windows on Azure (from Template)
resources.long_description:
This template allows you to deploy a simple Windows VM using a few different options for the Windows version, using the latest patched version. This will deploy a D1 size VM in the resource group location and return the fully qualified domain name of the VM.

See https://github.com/Azure/azure-quickstart-templates/tree/master/101-vm-simple-windows

resources.name: RHEL7 on Azure (from Template)
resources.long_description:
This template allows deploying a Red Hat Enterprise Linux VM (RHEL 7.2 or RHEL 6.7), using the latest image for the selected RHEL version. This will deploy a Standard D1 VM in the location of your chosen resource group with an additional 100 GiB data disk attached to the VM.

See https://github.com/Azure/azure-quickstart-templates/tree/master/101-vm-simple-rhel
